text:
Jerry Relph (September 4, 1944 − December 18, 2020) was an American politician. He was a member of the Republican Party. Relph was born in Boston, Massachusetts. Relph was a member of the Minnesota Senate from 2017 until his death.
Relph died on December 18, 2020 in St. Cloud, Minnesota from COVID-19 at the age of 76.
